<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11922] Persistent tail tracking picks random tail tracker from mongoDB collection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11922</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello. issue partially was fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8063&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8063&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was fixed in initialize() but still present in persistToStore() function&lt;br/&gt;
Bson updateObj = Updates.set(config.field, lastVal);&lt;br/&gt;
dbCol.updateOne(trackingObj, updateObj);&lt;br/&gt;
trackingObj = dbCol.find().first();&lt;br/&gt;
If more then one tracker is present in one collection, after storing lastVal, each trackingObj will replaced by first one from collection. Should be&lt;br/&gt;
trackingObj = dbCol.find(filter).first();&lt;br/&gt;
Issue present in version 2.20 in both mongodb and mongodb3 component.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
